		{
			dependencies: [
				"18592710C935A9C9"
				"497CC95523D1F210"
			]
			description: [
				"Fish may have different food preferences, but if you mash enough food-like stuff together, you can get something that will please most of them. &9Marine food&r can be used to tame most tameable aquatic animals, such as &aMantis Shrimps&r, &aMudskippers&r, or &aAxolotls&r."
				""
				"To make it, you'll need &9worms&r for the nutrition, with a dash of &9sugar&r to add flavor. And of course, all fish food has some &9ash&r in it (really, look at the nutrition analysis sometime), which you can obtain by smelting down &9compressed cobblestone&r into its basic inorganic elements. Mix that all together, and you've got a nice generic food. It's got what fish crave!"
				""
				"Alas, it is not healthy enough to make them breed."
			]
			id: "1023B9A16DFDA09C"
			subtitle: "kinda squishy"
			tasks: [{
				count: 32L
				id: "42306082C0EA1973"
				item: {
					Count: 32
					id: "kubejs:marine_food"
					tag: { }
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -4.0d
			y: -13.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1023B9A16DFDA09C"]
			description: ["&aSeals&r a friendly creatures that hang around on the shore. They love &9fish&r. If thrown 3 &9fish&r or &9marine foods&r, they will search around in the water for something to repay you with."]
